Q3. Consent:
Thank you for taking the time to participate in this study.

This study seeks to better understand risk preferences and general, related attitudes. In this study, you will be presented with a hypothetical scenario, requiring a choice between two options.  You will then be asked a few general questions regarding risk and general attitudes and preferences. There are no right or wrong answers.

The study should take you around 5 - 10 minutes to complete. You can withdraw from the study at any stage without explanation.

Your privacy is very important. Only the primary researcher will have access to the data. Results from this study will be used for the researcher’s MSc dissertation. Results and any data will be aggregated and anonymized, without any means of identifying the individuals involved. Data confidentiality will be protected in line with the LSE Research Privacy Policy. This project is in line with the ethical guidelines established by the Research Ethics Committee of the London School of Economics and Political Science (LSE).  If you have any questions you'd like to ask before starting the survey, please feel free to contact Anna King at a.king6@lse.ac.uk.



IMPORTANT: In order to participate in this study, you need to be 18+ and speak English fluently.

If you have read all of the above, and are happy to participate, please check the box “Yes, I provide my consent and want to take part.”
